10 substantial or serious bodily injury must be determined in accordance with section
11 12.1-02-05.
12 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 39-08-01.4 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 39-08-01.4. Driving while under the influence of alcohol or any other drugs or
15 substances while being accompanied by a minor - Penalty.
16 1. It is a class A misdemeanor for an individual who is at least twenty-one years of age to
17 violate section 39-08-01 if the violation occurred while a minor was accompanying the
18 individual in a motor vehicle. If an individual has a previous conviction for a violation of
19 section 39-08-01.4, a violation of this section is a class C felony. An individual
20 convicted under this section must be sentenced in accordance with subsection 5 of
21 section 39-08-01.
22 2. The minimum sentence for an individual convicted of violating this section must
23 include:
24 a. For a first offense, a fine of seven hundred fifty dollars, at least two days'
25 imprisonment, an order for a substance abuse evaluation by an appropriate
26 licensed addiction treatment program, at least three hundred sixty days of
27 unsupervised probation, and at least three hundred sixty days' participation in the
28 twenty - four seven sobriety program under chapter 54 - 12 as a mandatory
29 condition of probation.
30 b. For a second or subsequent offense within fifteen years, at least one year and
31 one day's imprisonment, a fine of two thousand dollars, an order for a substance
